The paper proposes a new method for tensor completion, which is a problem commonly studied in machine learning and computer vision. The paper focuses on the use of a new latent nuclear norm for inducing low-rank structure in tensors, which is a technique commonly used in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of sparsity structures and closed-form solutions, which are techniques commonly used in the fields of data science (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the time and space complexity of the proposed method, which is a topic commonly studied in numerical analysis (cs.NA).
